a must read this remarkable , very readable book is written as a conversation between two women born in beijing at the same time as the people 's republic of china . as the women explore the similarities and differences in their experiences -- from housing arrangements , to elementary school , to their roles in the early months of the cultural revolution , to the years spent working in rural china -- the reader learns about the wide range of what it means to have grown up in the prc . the result is a reflective , thought-full , and nuanced look at this tumultuous period in china 's recent history